---
import Features from '~/components/widgets/Features.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'SNN Lab Projects/Data-KSAH',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero>
    <Fragment slot="title"> Projects: KSAH </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
        <img
          src="/ksahlogo.png"
          alt="KSAH Logo"
          style="max-width: 680px; width: 100%; height: auto; margin-bottom: 2rem;"
        />
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <!-- Features Widget *************** -->

  <Features classes={{ container: 'pt-0 mt-0 -mt-40' }} title="Korean Study of Adolescent Health(KSAH)">
    <Fragment slot="subtitle">
      The Korean Study of Adolescent Health (KSAH) is built on a uniquely rich longitudinal data infrastructure that
      integrates genetic, neuroimaging, and complete social network information from multiple cohorts of a Korean girl's
      high school students. The study combines genome-wide SNP data derived from saliva samples, repeated structural and
      functional MRI scans capturing brain development and socioemotional processing, and real-name friendship networks
      collected at multiple time points to track network formation and change. These biological and social data are
      linked to repeated self-reported measures of mental health, including stress, anxiety, depression, problem
      behaviors, suicidal ideation, and sleep quality. By synchronizing genetic predispositions, neural development, and
      evolving peer relationships within a single cohort-based design, KSAH enables rigorous longitudinal and causal
      analyses of adolescent mental health across multiple levels of explanation.

      <h3 style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">[Key Data Components]</h3>

      <ul style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-left: 1.25rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <strong>Genetics</strong>
          <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-left: 1.6rem;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">- Saliva samples collected from over 130 participants</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">
              - Genome-wide SNP data (~500,000 variants) using Korean-optimized genotyping arrays
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">- Polygenic Risk Scores (PRS) calculated using GWAS methods</li>
          </ul>
        </li>

        <li style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <strong>Brain Imaging</strong>
          <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-left: 1.6rem;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">
              - Structural MRI (T1, DTI) and functional MRI (resting-state and task-based)
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">
              - Face-viewing and movie-watching paradigms to capture social and emotional processing
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">- Repeated measurements enabling developmental trajectory analysis</li>
          </ul>
        </li>

        <li style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <strong>Social Network Data</strong>
          <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-left: 1.6rem;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">
              - Complete, real-name friendship networks collected through repeated surveys
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">
              - Longitudinal network tracking of network dynamics, reciprocity, and structural change
            </li>
          </ul>
        </li>

        <li style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
          <strong>Mental Health Measures</strong>
          <ul style="margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-left: 1.6rem;">
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">
              - Self-reported indicators of stress, anxiety, depression, problem behaviors
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">- Measures of suicidal ideation and sleep quality</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; margin-top: 2rem;">
        <img
          src="/ksahprojdesc.png"
          alt="KSAH Project Overview"
          style="max-width: 900px; width: 100%; height: auto; margin-bottom: 2rem;"
        />
      </div>

      <div style="margin-top: 2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem;">
        <strong>Official Links</strong>
        <a
          href="https://www.krm.or.kr/krmts/link.html?dbGubun=SD&m201_id=10100615&local_id=10114533"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          style="font-weight: 600; text-decoration: underline;"
        >
          National Research Foundation (NRF / KRM) Project Record
        </a>
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </Features>
</Layout>
